d.duplicated <- d %>% mutate(survey_month = format(created_at_app, "%Y-%m")) %>% 
  get_dupes(user_id, survey_month) %>% 
  select(user_id, survey_month, dupe_count) %>%
  distinct()

n_dupes <- d.duplicated %>%
  summarise(n_dupes = sum(dupe_count))

expected_rows <- nrow(d) - (n_dupes - nrow(d.duplicated))
d <- d %>%
  mutate(survey_month = format(created_at_app, "%Y-%m")) %>% 
  mutate(missingness = rowSums(is.na(.))/ncol(.)) %>%
  group_by(user_id, survey_month) %>%
  slice(which.min(missingness)) %>%
  ungroup()

Model-based clustering

 d.closed <- d.closed %>%
   rename_with(~ str_wrap(unlist(d.closed.questions), 30), all_of(names(d.closed.questions))) 

class(d.closed)="data.frame"

# Cluster analysis without variable selection
res_without <- VarSelCluster(d.closed, gvals = 1:5, nbcores = 4, vbleSelec = FALSE, crit.varsel = "BIC")

d.cluster <- d %>%
  drop_na(q2_response_app) %>%
  mutate(class = factor(fitted(res_without)))

d.cluster %>%
  select(class, matches("users_"), q2_response_app, q4_response_app, q2_response_link) %>%
  rownames_to_column() %>%
  arrange(class) %>%
  gather(colname, value, -rowname, -class) %>%
  ggplot(aes(x = rowname, y = colname, fill = value, group=class)) +
  geom_tile() + theme(legend.position = "none") +
  facet_wrap(.~class) +
  theme(axis.text.x=element_blank())

# https://methodenlehre.github.io/SGSCLM-R-course/descriptive-statistics.html#descriptive-statistics-for-nominal-variables

perc_scale = function(x) (x/1)

d.cluster %>%
  drop_na(q2_response_app) %>%
  group_by(class, q2_response_app) %>%
  summarise(n = n()) %>%
  mutate(freq = round( n / sum(n), 2)) %>%
  select(-n) %>%
  spread(class, freq, drop=T) %>%
  mutate_all(funs(replace_na(.,0))) %>%
  formattable(list('1' = color_bar("#e9c46a",  fun = perc_scale), 
                   '2' = color_bar("#80ed99",  fun = perc_scale), 
                   '3' = color_bar("#48cae4",  fun = perc_scale)))

d.cluster %>%
  select(class, q2_response_app, q4_response_app) %>%
  mutate_at(vars(starts_with("q")), as.numeric) %>%
  group_by(class) %>%
  summarise(across(
    .cols = is.numeric, 
    .fns = list(Mean = mean, SD = sd), na.rm = TRUE, 
    .names = "{col}_{fn}"
    )) %>%
  mutate(q2_response_app_Mean = paste(round(q2_response_app_Mean, 2), "", round(q2_response_app_SD, 2)),
         q4_response_app_Mean = paste(round(q4_response_app_Mean, 2), "", round(q4_response_app_SD, 2))) %>%
  select(-contains("SD")) %>% formattable()
